  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you were-- you were taking-- you were taking, like, bed-- bedding.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were taking, like, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] your worldly possessions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You became very creative, as-- as I will tell you in my next phase of this tale, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You took the things that you thought would-- would serve you best after his speech.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whether you believed it or not, you did go along with that, just in case.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we schlepped the pillow, this, and some clothes, some shoes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Shoes were very valuable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You don't go into a store and buy ready-made shoes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every shoe you-- we wear and we wore was fitted and made by a schuster, by a shoemaker.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So these were valuable things.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And clothing.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So in terms of what did we take, it was enough that you can carry, not [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] have someone carry for you or put it on some sort of a-- a transportation vehicle.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my dad took his-- he was a-- he was an excellent accordio-- accordion player, so he took his accordion.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother took-- she was a sew-- seamstress, too, and she knew, so she took some of that thing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sister was-- schlepped whatever she could, and I took whatever I could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we just carried as much as we could to the train, to the-- to the place where we met to get on the trains.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 13 SECONDS] If there is such a thing as intuition-- like a seventh, eighth, ninth sense of something, that you know in some sort of capacity that something bad is going to happen, something is now developing-- I can tell you without any hesitation that a child feels that as well as an adult.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
